      <h1>Unlock the Full Power of RSOLV</h1>

      <p>Hi {@first_name},</p>

      <p>
        You've been using RSOLV for a few days now. Here are some advanced features and techniques that can help you get even more value from automated security scanning and vulnerability remediation:
      </p>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <h3>üéØ Understanding RSOLV's Proactive Scanning</h3>
        <p>
          RSOLV continuously scans your repositories for security vulnerabilities and automatically creates issues with detailed remediation plans:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Automated detection:</strong>
            Scans all files for 180+ vulnerability patterns (and growing)
          </li>
          <li><strong>Smart grouping:</strong> Groups similar issues for efficient review</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Detailed reports:</strong> Shows exact file locations and vulnerable code
          </li>
          <li><strong>Fix generation:</strong> Creates secure PRs that address root causes</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <h3>üîí Comprehensive Security Coverage</h3>
        <p>RSOLV proactively detects and fixes these vulnerability types across your codebase:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>SQL/NoSQL injection vulnerabilities</li>
          <li>Cross-site scripting (XSS) risks</li>
          <li>Authentication/authorization flaws</li>
          <li>Insecure cryptographic implementations</li>
          <li>Hardcoded secrets and API keys</li>
          <li>Path traversal and open redirects</li>
          <li>Insecure dependencies and configurations</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Each PR includes a detailed security impact assessment and verification tests.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="security-highlight">
        <strong>üõ°Ô∏è Security Example:</strong>
        When RSOLV detects unsafe user input handling, it automatically generates fixes with proper sanitization, parameterized queries, and input validation to prevent injection attacks.
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <h3>üöÄ Efficient Issue Management</h3>
        <p>RSOLV's proactive scanning creates organized, actionable issues:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Smart grouping:</strong> Similar vulnerabilities are grouped together</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Priority labeling:</strong> Issues labeled by severity (HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW)
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Automated PR generation:</strong>
            Each issue can trigger a fix PR with the "rsolv:automate" label
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Batch review:</strong> Review and merge multiple security fixes efficiently
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>You maintain full control - review each PR before merging.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <h3>üìä Understanding RSOLV's PR Structure</h3>
        <p>Every RSOLV PR includes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Summary:</strong> What was fixed and why</li>
          <li><strong>Changes:</strong> File-by-file breakdown</li>
          <li><strong>Security Analysis:</strong> Any vulnerabilities addressed</li>
          <li><strong>Testing:</strong> Suggested test cases</li>
          <li><strong>Educational Notes:</strong> Learn about the fix</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="pro-tip">
        <strong>üí° Pro Tip:</strong>
        Use descriptive branch protection rules! RSOLV respects your branch protection settings, so PRs will go through your normal review process.
      </div>

